## Prioritized Remediation

| Priority | Smell | Effort | Why first |
|----------|-------|--------|-----------|
| 1 | Assertion-Free Test | Low | False confidence — tests pass but verify nothing |
| 2 | Conditional Test Logic | Low | Hidden gap — one branch is untested |
| 3 | Mystery Guest | Low | Broken on every machine except the author's |
| 4 | Exception Handling | Low | One-line refactor to `ThrowsException` |
| 5 | Sleepy Test | Medium | Flaky in CI, slows the suite |
| 6 | Magic Numbers / Assertion Roulette | Medium | Readability + diagnosis difficulty |
| 7 | Sensitive Equality | Medium | Brittleness to formatting changes |
| 8 | Eager Test | Medium | Requires design decision on splitting |
| 9 | General Fixture | Low | Cleanup — remove unused `_logger` |

Items 1–4 are quick wins you can fix in minutes. Items 5–8 require a bit more thought but pay off in reduced flakiness and maintainability.
